== Project

*Learning in games, last-iterate, Blackwell approachability theorem*
[https://github.com/caihuaiguang/PIDCFR/blob/main/pic/full.pdf \[Results\]]\n
Experimentally observed that predictive CFR algorithms converge much faster in last-iterate than in average-iterate in non-HUNL two-player zero-sum games.
I am now working on connecting the Proportional-Integral-Derivative (PID) algorithm in control theory with the Counterfactual Regret Minimization (CFR) algorithm in game theory by developing a last-iterate version of the Blackwell approachability theorem.\n



